Optimized for move-in/out, cleaning checks, maintenance follow-ups, and evidence logging.

# **1\. User Roles** {#1.-user-roles}

### 1\. Guest (Try Demo) {#1.-guest-(try-demo)}

* No login  
* Choose role (Inspector / Cleaner / Manager)  
* Access demo data & demo flows

### 2\. Cleaner / Service Staff {#2.-cleaner-/-service-staff}

* Upload before/after photos  
* See assigned tasks only  
* Mark tasks as completed

### Provide evidence (“Pending Proof to Verified”) {#provide-evidence-(“pending-proof-to-verified”)}

### 3\. Inspector Staff {#3.-inspector-staff}

* Capture photos & notes  
* Confirm Report generated  
* Share report via emails

### 4.Property Manager / Housing Manager {#4.property-manager-/-housing-manager}

* Create inspection templates  
* Assign inspections  
* Review and verify submitted reports  
* Track team productivity & time saved  
* Manage team accounts & permissions  
* Export data to Vitec, Planima, FAST2, Brive, POB, etc. \[Optional, low priority for current version\]


# **2\. Core Product Modules** {#2.-core-product-modules}

| \# | Module | Description (Short) | Priority |
| ----- | ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **1** | Gemini 3 AI Module | Core multimodal AI pipeline for per-photo analysis & report generation | P0 – Critical |
| **2** | Inspections Module | Create inspections, capture photos, store evidence, trigger AI | P0 – Critical |
| **3** | AI Report Generation Module | Build inspection reports from AI output and generate PDF | P1 – High |
| **4** | Public Landing & Onboarding Module | Landing page \+ demo onboarding (“Try as Manager/Inspector/Cleaner”) | P1 – High |
| **5** | Task Routing & Work Orders Module | AI-driven cleaning/maintenance tasks with evidence upload | P2 – Medium |
| **6** | Evidence Log Module | Centralized evidence archive with filtering, search, and exports | P2 – Medium |
| **7** | Team Management & Account Module | User roles, invites, permissions, organization settings | P3 – Low |

# **2.1. Public Landing & Onboarding Module** {#2.1.-public-landing-&-onboarding-module}

*(Former Module 7 — now Module 1\)*

### **Purpose** {#purpose}

Provide frictionless entry into Verispect with “Try Without Signup” role options, enabling instant evaluation and demo usage.

### **Responsibilities** {#responsibilities}

* Serve the marketing site

* Provide three demo entry points:

  * Try as Manager

  * Try as Inspector

  * Try as Cleaner

* Initialize demo environments with mock data

* Gate “full account creation” behind signup modal

* Deliver sample PDF report generation (static or AI-backed)

  ### **Key Components** {#key-components}

* `/landing` public route

* `/try/<role>` dynamic demo loader

* Signup modal (email \+ password)

* No credit card required

* Demo expiration (optional)

  ### **Developer Notes** {#developer-notes}

* Demo mode uses a separate demo tenant in the DB

* Demo role determines which dashboard loads

* AI calls in demo mode use sample images OR reduced-rate pipeline

  # **2.2. Gemini 3 AI Module** {#2.2.-gemini-3-ai-module}

  ### **Purpose** {#purpose-1}

Provide a centralized AI pipeline that performs image understanding, issue detection, report generation, task recommendation, and text structuring.

### **Responsibilities** {#responsibilities-1}

1. **Per-Photo Analysis** (Image to Structured JSON)

2. **Inspection-Level Report Generation** (Evidence JSON to Written Report)

3. **Task Routing Recommendations**

4. **Checklist Auto-Population**

5. **Structured Output** for PDF builder

   ### **Endpoints** {#endpoints}

* `POST /ai/analyze_photo`

* `POST /ai/generate_report`

* `POST /ai/recommend_tasks`

  ### **AI Workflow (Gemini 3\)** {#ai-workflow-(gemini-3)}

  #### **A. Per-Photo Processing** {#a.-per-photo-processing}

Input:

* Image (JPEG/PNG)  
* Optional inspector note  
* Inspection ID

Output stored in DB:

`{`

  `"room": "Bathroom",`

  `"issues": [`

    `{ "type": "mold", "severity": "high", "details": "Ceiling area" }`

  `],`

  `"cleanliness": "dirty",`

 `"objects": ["sink", "shower", "mirror"],`

 `"description": "Mold visible on ceiling and unclean tiles."`

`}`

#### **B. Report Generation (Final Inspection)** {#b.-report-generation-(final-inspection)}

Input:

* Array of evidence JSON  
* Unit metadata  
* Inspection type

Output:

* Room-by-room narrative  
* Issues list  
* Cleaning tasks  
* Maintenance tasks  
* Report text blocks  
* Structured JSON for PDF generation

  #### **C. Task Recommendation** {#c.-task-recommendation}

Rules \+ AI classification:

* Dirt or cleanliness issue recommends cleaning task  
* Damage issue recommends maintenance task

  ### **Developer Notes** {#developer-notes-1}

* All AI calls routed through a single `Gemini3Client` wrapper  
* Idempotency key recommended for retry-safe calls  
* Strict JSON schema validation required before saving to DB

  # **2.3. Inspections Module** {#2.3.-inspections-module}

  ### **Purpose** {#purpose-2}

Handle the full inspection lifecycle from creation to photo capture to AI analysis to manager verification.

### **Responsibilities** {#responsibilities-2}

* Create new inspections  
* Assign inspectors  
* Track inspection statuses  
* Upload photos  
* Trigger AI analysis per photo  
* Manage drafts, signatures, and verification  
* Store and link AI evidence to inspections

  ### **States**  {#states}

* `IN_PROGRESS`  
* `PENDING APPROVAL`  
* `VERIFIED`

  ### **Key Components** {#key-components-1}

* `/inspections` CRUD API  
* `/inspections/:id/photos` upload  
* Offline-first photo queue in frontend  
* AI-triggered event: `onPhotoUploaded to analyze_photo`

  ### **Developer Notes** {#developer-notes-2}

* Evidence stored in `evidence_items` table  
* Images stored in S3 with signed URLs  
* Inspection belongs to a tenant (multi-tenancy)

  # **2.4. AI Report Generation Module** {#2.4.-ai-report-generation-module}

  ### **Purpose** {#purpose-3}

Transform all collected evidence into a final, structured, dispute-proof inspection report.

### **Responsibilities** {#responsibilities-3}

* Receive final AI output from Gemini 3  
* Build report JSON structure  
* Pass to PDF builder  
* Store final report in `reports` table  
* Provide manager approval UI  
* Support sharing/printing/downloading

  ### **Outputs** {#outputs}

* PDF file (stored in S3)  
* Online report viewer (HTML)  
* Checklist table  
* Issues table  
* Task lists

  ### **Developer Notes** {#developer-notes-3}

* QR code linking back to `/report/<id>`

  # **2.5. Task Routing & Work Orders Module** {#2.5.-task-routing-&-work-orders-module}

  ### **Purpose** {#purpose-4}

Simplify downstream workflows by assigning cleaning or maintenance tasks triggered by AI findings.

### **Responsibilities** {#responsibilities-4}

* Create tasks from AI output  
* Assign tasks to staff roles  
* Enable cleaners/technicians to upload before/after proof  
* Track statuses:

  * `Drafted`  
  * `PENDING_PROOF`  
  * `SUBMITTED`  
  * `VERIFIED`

* Link tasks back to issues and inspections

  ### **Endpoints** {#endpoints-1}

* `/tasks` CRUD  
* `/tasks/:id/upload`  
* `/tasks/:id/verify`

  ### **Developer Notes** {#developer-notes-4}

* Task-to-user assignment done via RBAC  
* Task category derived from AI module  
* Before/after evidence stored under `task_evidence` table

  # **2.6. Evidence Log Module** {#2.6.-evidence-log-module}

  ### **Purpose** {#purpose-5}

Provide a unified historical archive of all photos, issues, and AI-calculated metadata.

### **Responsibilities** {#responsibilities-5}

* Store all evidence items  
* Filter/search by:  
  * unit  
  * date  
  * inspector  
  * room  
  * issue type  
* Support deep inspection of issue history  
* Provide downloads and export  
* Link evidence to report references

  ### **Key Components** {#key-components-2}

* Evidence grid view  
* Evidence detail modal  
* AI metadata sidebar

  ### **Developer Notes** {#developer-notes-5}

* Index `issues->type` column for quick search  
* Pagination required (images scale fast)

  # **2.7. Team Management & Account Module** {#2.7.-team-management-&-account-module}

  ### **Purpose** {#purpose-6}

Manage multi-tenant environments, user roles, billing, and permissions.

### **Responsibilities** {#responsibilities-6}

* User account creation  
* Role assignment: `manager`, `inspector`, `cleaner`, `admin`  
* Team invites  
* Organization-level settings  
* Billing (later stage)  
* Subscription plans

  ### **Developer Notes** {#developer-notes-6}

* Follow RBAC model  
* Use JWT for session \+ role claims  
* Plan metadata can be feature-gated
